The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | 120 acres for knowledge
                                                                                                               120 acres for knowledge
                            
	Calcutta, Feb. 2: A knowledge hub spread over 120 acres will come up in the new 500-acre South 24-Parganas district headquarters in Baruipur, the government said today.        
	The decision to set up the hub had been taken along with the one to shift the headquarters from Alipore. Subesh Das, the principal secretary to the chief minister, today held a meeting with the science and technology secretary, experts working on the project and the local MP to finalise the land requirement. The government has over 500 acres there.         
	An official in the chief ministers secretariat said several research institutes had shown keen interest in the hub.                                                                                                                                                                             
